Preconditions:
- The input `n` is an even integer.
- The initial permutation `perm` is an array of size `n` where `perm[i] == i` for each index `i` (0-indexed).

Postconditions:
- The array `perm` has been modified to its initial value.
- The minimum non-zero number of operations needed to perform on `perm` to return it to its initial value has been returned as an integer.